Package: networkinference
Type: Package
Title: Post-selection inference with a single realization of a network
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Ethan Ancell
Maintainer: Ethan Ancell <ancell@uw.edu>
Description: Implementation of the methods the "Post-selection inference with a
    single realization of a network" paper. This package contains two crucial
    functions (split_network() and infer_network()) which split an adjacency
    matrix into two train and test adjacency matrices, and conduct inference
    for a linear combination of connectivity patterns based upon the estimated
    communities using the train network, respectively.
